<br>
Heh, most memorable moment ever for me would be the day my friends and I dropped Faydedar.<br>
<br>
Anyone else remember sweating buckets in RL the day you found Dolgin up and your friends would actually come help?<br>
<br>
Wow, what a rush, and the funniest thing about that day was the 2 level 60 wizards that were running out to help me beat the fish died on the raptor islands passing by.  60 Wizards... dying to raptors.<br>
<br>
<br>
I'd have to say the other &quot;signifigant&quot; event in my druid's career would be both the first time I ran through DL at level 18, and the first time I ran through WW to ToV.  (I didn't have a guide or nothing.  Just a map.)  I was sweating a cold sweat there.<br>
<br>
Far too many stories to tell I'm afraid.<br>
